@startuml
!theme plain
title Discord OAuth2 Login Flow (Current)

actor "User" as U
participant "Browser" as B
participant "Axum App" as A
participant "Redis (Ephemeral)" as R
participant "Discord OAuth2" as D

== Step 1: User initiates login ==
U -> B : Click "Login with Discord"
B -> A : GET /login

== Step 2: Generate session & secrets ==
A -> A : Generate session_id (UUID)\nGenerate PKCE challenge & verifier\nGenerate CSRF token

== Step 3: Store OAuth session in Redis ==
A -> R : store_oauth_session(\n  session_id,\n  csrf_token,\n  pkce_verifier,\n  nonce="",\n  expiry=10min\n)

== Step 4: Build OAuth2 client and auth URL ==
A -> A : create_oauth_client(AppState)
A -> A : Build authorization URL with:\n- PKCE challenge\n- CSRF token\n- Scopes: identify, email

== Step 5: Set session cookie ==
A -> B : Set "session_id" cookie\n(httpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Lax, max-age=1h)

== Step 6: Redirect to Discord ==
A -> B : Redirect to Discord OAuth2 URL
B -> D : Request authorization page

@enduml
